The paper discusses learning-to-learn or meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that falls under several categories in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on gradient-based meta-learning, which is a popular approach in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
